  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed development by reason of its design, scale, massing and position would result in an obtrusive and incompatible form of development that would fail to respect the character and appearance of the subject property, the setting of the adjacent Locally Listed building at no. 103 Wick Road and the character and appearance of the wider streetscene. As such, the proposed development is contrary to policies D3 (Optimising site capacity through the design-led approach), D4 (Delivering good design) and HC1 (Heritage conservation and growth) of the London Plan 2021, policies LP1 (Design Quality and Local Character), LP4 (Non Designated Heritage Assets) and LP17 (Housing Design) of the Hackney Local Plan 2033 (2020), and the guidance contained within Hackney Residential Extensions and Alterations SPD (2009).",
    "The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a contribution towards affordable housing fails to deliver the maximum reasonable amount of affordable housing and is therefore contrary to policy H4 (Delivering affordable housing) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP13 (Affordable housing) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#39;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).",
    "The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure car-free housing, would be likely to promote the use of non-sustainable modes of transport and contribute to air pollution and congestion in the surrounding area, contrary to policy T6 of the London Plan (2021), policy LP45 (Parking and Car Free Development) and LP58 (Improving the Environment - Pollution) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#39;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020).",
    "The proposed development, in the absence of a legal agreement to secure a carbon offset contribution, would fail to mitigate the impact of the development on climate change and maximise sustainable development contrary to contrary to policy SI2 (Minimising Greenhouse Gas Emissions) of the London Plan (2021), policy LP55 (Mitigating Climate Change) of Hackney’s Local Plan 2033 (2020) and Hackney&#39;s S106 Planning Contributions SPD (2020)."
  ],
